Reassigning to engine team. Some suggestions from Zhiqiang:

Current IDataRowExpressionEvaluator.first() doesn?t have a return value. This causes a bug in DataProcessor when binding the data. The code is in mapToChartResultSet():



                     idre.first( );



                     do

                     {

                            oaTuple = new Object[iColumnCount];

                            it = co.iterator( );

                            iColumnIndex = 0;

                            while ( it.hasNext( ) )

                            {

                                   oaTuple[iColumnIndex++] = idre.evaluate( (String) it.next( ) );

                            }

                            liResultSet.add( oaTuple );

                     } while ( idre.next( ) );



So with this, even the IRowSet doesn?t have any row, the chart ResultSet will have one null row, this is not correct.



I think we should change it to Boolean first(); And also you can see in java.sql.ResultSet, the first() method has a return value to indicate if current cursor is in a valid position.



And after we change the interface. This code will be:



              boolean hasFirst = idre.first( );



              if ( hasFirst )

              {

                     do

                     {

                            oaTuple = new Object[iColumnCount];

                            it = co.iterator( );

                            iColumnIndex = 0;

                            while ( it.hasNext( ) )

                            {

                                   oaTuple[iColumnIndex++] = idre.evaluate( (String) it.next( ) );

                            }

                            liResultSet.add( oaTuple );

                     } while ( idre.next( ) );

              }



Now it will be correct for this case.



This change will involve all the IDataRowExpressionEvaluator implementation, including SqlDataRowEvaluator, BirtDataRowEvaluator, and one anonymous implementation in ChartUIUtil.
